{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1204,"text":"Good afternoon, I'm proud\nto be here at TEDxKrakow."},{"time":4329,"text":"I'll try to speak a little bit today\nabout a phenomenon"},{"time":7350,"text":"which can, and actually is\nchanging the world,"},{"time":10376,"text":"and whose name is people power."},{"time":12392,"text":"I'll start with an anecdote,"},{"time":13924,"text":"or for those of you\nwho are Monty Python lovers,"},{"time":17071,"text":"a Monty Python type of sketch."},{"time":18542,"text":"Here it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19597,"text":"It is December 15, 2010."},{"time":22756,"text":"Somebody gives you a bet:\nyou will look at a crystal ball,"},{"time":26262,"text":"and you will see the future;\nthe future will be accurate."},{"time":28953,"text":"But you need to share it with the world."},{"time":30897,"text":"OK, curiosity killed the cat,\nyou take the bet,"},{"time":34019,"text":"you look at the crystal ball."},{"time":35553,"text":"One hour later, you're sitting\nin a building of the national TV,"},{"time":39116,"text":"in a top show, and you tell the story."},{"time":41672,"text":"Before the end of 2011,"},{"time":44780,"text":"Ben Ali, and Mubarak,\nand Gaddafi would be down,"},{"time":48953,"text":"and prosecuted."},{"time":50705,"text":"Saleh of Yemen and Assad of Syria"},{"time":53221,"text":"would be either challenged,\nor already on their knees."},{"time":56683,"text":"Osama bin Laden would be dead,"},{"time":58701,"text":"and Ratko Mladic would be in the Hague."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61421,"text":"Now, the anchor watches you\nwith a strange gaze on his face."},{"time":64991,"text":"And then, on top of it you add:"},{"time":66833,"text":"\"And thousands of young people\nfrom Athens, Madrid and New York"},{"time":70722,"text":"will demonstrate for social justice,\nclaiming they are inspired by Arabs.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":76007,"text":"Next thing you know,\ntwo guys in white appear,"},{"time":78587,"text":"they give you the strange t-shirt,"},{"time":80825,"text":"take you to the nearest\nmental institution."},{"time":82904,"text":"So I would like to speak a little bit"},{"time":84791,"text":"about the phenomenon which is behind\nwhat already seems to be"},{"time":88664,"text":"a very bad year for bad guys."},{"time":91379,"text":"And this phenomenon\nis called people power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94780,"text":"Well, people power\nhas been there for a while."},{"time":96947,"text":"It helped Gandhi kick\nthe Brits from India,"},{"time":99942,"text":"it helped Martin Luther King\nwin his historic racial struggle."},{"time":104073,"text":"It helped a local, Lech Walesa,"},{"time":106460,"text":"to kick out one million\nSoviet troops from Poland,"},{"time":109880,"text":"and in beginning the end\nof the Soviet Union as we know it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113102,"text":"So what's new in it?"},{"time":115157,"text":"What seems to be very new,"},{"time":116765,"text":"which is the idea I would like\nto share with you today,"},{"time":119361,"text":"is that there is a set of rules and skills"},{"time":121823,"text":"which can be learned and taught"},{"time":124305,"text":"in order to perform\nsuccessful nonviolent struggle."},{"time":127753,"text":"If this is true, we can help\nthese movements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131531,"text":"Well, the first one - analytic skills."},{"time":134374,"text":"I'll try where it all started\nin the Middle East."},{"time":137224,"text":"And for so many years,"},{"time":138846,"text":"we were living with a completely wrong\nperception of the Middle East."},{"time":143274,"text":"It was looking like the frozen region."},{"time":145201,"text":"Literally a refrigerator."},{"time":146934,"text":"And there were only\ntwo types of meal there."},{"time":149401,"text":"Steak, which stands for a Mubarak-Ben Ali\ntype of military police dictatorship,"},{"time":155279,"text":"or a potato, which stands for\na Tehran type of theocracies."},{"time":158957,"text":"And everybody was amazed\nwhen the refrigerator opened,"},{"time":162291,"text":"and millions of young,\nmainly secular people"},{"time":165246,"text":"stepped out to do the change."},{"time":167320,"text":"Guess what - they didn't watch\nthe demographics."},{"time":170731,"text":"What is the average age\nof an Egyptian? 24."},{"time":173147,"text":"How long was Mubarak in power? 31."},{"time":175530,"text":"So, this system was just\nobsolete, they expired."},{"time":179437,"text":"And young people of the Arab world\nhave awakened one morning,"},{"time":182871,"text":"and understood that power\nlies in their hands."},{"time":186226,"text":"The rest is the year in front of us."},{"time":188273,"text":"And guess what? The same Generation Y,"},{"time":191145,"text":"with their rules, with their tools,\nwith their games,"},{"time":194051,"text":"and with their language,\nwhich sounds a little bit strange to me."},{"time":197389,"text":"I'm 38 now."},{"time":199257,"text":"And can you look at the age\nof the people on the streets of Europe?"},{"time":202794,"text":"It seems that Generation Y is coming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207025,"text":"Now, let me set another example."},{"time":209738,"text":"I'm meeting different people\nthroughout the world,"},{"time":212119,"text":"and they are, you know, academics,\nand professors, and doctors,"},{"time":215270,"text":"and they will always talk conditions."},{"time":217168,"text":"They will say: \"People power will work\nonly if the regime is not too oppressive.\""},{"time":221221,"text":"They will say: \"People power will work,"},{"time":223230,"text":"if the annual income of the country\nis between X and Z.\""},{"time":227070,"text":"They will say: \"People power will work\nonly if there is a foreign pressure.\""},{"time":230744,"text":"They will say: \"People power\nwill work only if there is no oil.\""},{"time":233850,"text":"And, I mean, there is a set of conditions."},{"time":236958,"text":"Well, the news here\nis that your skills during the conflict"},{"time":240608,"text":"seem to be more important\nthan the conditions."},{"time":243522,"text":"Namely, the skills of unity, planning,\nand maintaining nonviolent discipline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248133,"text":"Let me give you an example."},{"time":249546,"text":"I come from a country called Serbia."},{"time":251631,"text":"It took us 10 years to unite\n18 opposition party leaders,"},{"time":256209,"text":"with their big egos,\nbehind one single candidate"},{"time":259613,"text":"against the Balkan dictator\nSlobodan Milosevic."},{"time":262264,"text":"Guess what? That was\nthe day of his defeat."},{"time":265034,"text":"You look at the Egyptians,\nthey fight on Tahrir Square,"},{"time":267923,"text":"they get rid of their individual symbols,"},{"time":270007,"text":"they appear on the street\nonly with the flag of Egypt."},{"time":272926,"text":"I will give you a counter-example."},{"time":274967,"text":"You see nine presidential candidates\nrunning against Lukashenko,"},{"time":278681,"text":"you all know the outcome."},{"time":280284,"text":"So unity is a big thing."},{"time":282398,"text":"And this can be achieved."},{"time":283724,"text":"Same with planning."},{"time":284930,"text":"Somebody has lied to you"},{"time":286325,"text":"about the successful and spontaneous\nnonviolent revolution."},{"time":290102,"text":"That thing doesn't exist in the world."},{"time":292133,"text":"Whenever you see young people\nin front of the row"},{"time":295006,"text":"trying to fraternize\nwith the police or military,"},{"time":297506,"text":"somebody was thinking about it before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300016,"text":"Now, at the end, nonviolent discipline."},{"time":302229,"text":"And this is probably the game-changer."},{"time":304722,"text":"If you maintain nonviolent discipline,"},{"time":307116,"text":"you'll exclusively win."},{"time":309098,"text":"You have 100,000 people\nin a nonviolent march,"},{"time":311582,"text":"one idiot or agent-provocateur\nthrowing a stone."},{"time":314360,"text":"Guess what takes all the cameras."},{"time":316094,"text":"That one guy."},{"time":317212,"text":"One single act of violence\ncan literally destroy your movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321564,"text":"Now, let me move to another place."},{"time":324175,"text":"It's the selection\nof strategies and tactics."},{"time":326295,"text":"There are certain rules\nin nonviolent struggle you may follow."},{"time":330113,"text":"First, you start small."},{"time":331765,"text":"Second, you pick the battles you can win."},{"time":335181,"text":"It's only 200 of us in this room."},{"time":337212,"text":"We won't call for the march of a million."},{"time":339553,"text":"But what if we organized the spraying\nof graffiti throughout the night,"},{"time":343001,"text":"all over Krakow."},{"time":344432,"text":"The city will know."},{"time":345600,"text":"So, we pick tactics\naccommodated to the event,"},{"time":348925,"text":"especially this thing we call\nthe small tactics of dispersion."},{"time":352996,"text":"They're very useful in violent oppression."},{"time":356933,"text":"We are actually witnessing the picture\nof one of the best tactics ever used."},{"time":361153,"text":"It was on Tahrir square,"},{"time":363248,"text":"where the international community\nwas constantly frightened"},{"time":366548,"text":"that, you know, the Islamists\nwill overtake the revolution."},{"time":369735,"text":"What they organized --"},{"time":371132,"text":"Christians protecting Muslims\nwhere they are praying,"},{"time":373633,"text":"a Coptic wedding cheered\nby thousands of Muslims,"},{"time":376245,"text":"the world has just changed the picture,"},{"time":378289,"text":"but somebody was thinking\nabout this previously."},{"time":381313,"text":"So there are so many things you can do"},{"time":383267,"text":"instead of getting into one place,"},{"time":385608,"text":"shouting, and you know, showing off\nin front of the security forces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391013,"text":"Now, there is also another\nvery important dynamic."},{"time":393983,"text":"And this is a dynamic\nthat analysts normally don't see."},{"time":397260,"text":"This is the dynamic between\nfear and apathy on the one side,"},{"time":400981,"text":"and enthusiasm and humor on another side."},{"time":403917,"text":"So, it works like in a video game."},{"time":405671,"text":"You have the fear high,\nyou have status quo."},{"time":408079,"text":"You have the enthusiasm higher,"},{"time":410167,"text":"you see the fear is starting to melt."},{"time":412001,"text":"Day two, you see people\nrunning towards the police"},{"time":414747,"text":"instead of from the police, in Egypt."},{"time":417332,"text":"You can tell that something\nis happening there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419936,"text":"And then, it's about the humor."},{"time":421945,"text":"Humor is such a powerful game-changer,"},{"time":424452,"text":"and of course, it was very big in Poland."},{"time":426449,"text":"You know, we were just a small group\nof crazy students in Serbia"},{"time":430016,"text":"when we made this big skit."},{"time":432156,"text":"We put the big petrol barrel"},{"time":434625,"text":"with a portrait of Mr. President on it,\nin the middle of the Main Street."},{"time":439312,"text":"There was a hole in the top."},{"time":440917,"text":"So you could literally come,\nput a coin in,"},{"time":443702,"text":"get a baseball bat, and hit his face."},{"time":447180,"text":"Sounds loud."},{"time":448861,"text":"And within minutes,"},{"time":450161,"text":"we were sitting in a nearby café\nhaving coffee,"},{"time":452542,"text":"and there was a queue of people\nwaiting to do this lovely thing."},{"time":456820,"text":"Well, that's just\nthe beginning of the show."},{"time":458892,"text":"The real show starts\nwhen the police appears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461049,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":462294,"text":"\"What will they do?\""},{"time":463452,"text":"Arrest us? We were nowhere to be seen."},{"time":465368,"text":"We were like three blocks away,\nobserving it from our espresso bar."},{"time":469207,"text":"Arrest the shoppers, with kids?"},{"time":471155,"text":"Doesn't make sense."},{"time":472385,"text":"Of course, you could bet,\nthey did the most stupid thing."},{"time":475076,"text":"They arrested the barrel."},{"time":476648,"text":"And now, the picture\nof the smashed face on the barrel,"},{"time":479590,"text":"with the policemen\ndragging it to the police car,"},{"time":481924,"text":"that was the best day\nfor newspaper photographers"},{"time":485147,"text":"that they will ever have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486851,"text":"So, I mean, these are\nthe things you can do."},{"time":489092,"text":"And you can always use humor."},{"time":490515,"text":"There is also one big thing about humor,"},{"time":492814,"text":"it really hurts."},{"time":494117,"text":"Because these guys really are\ntaking themselves too seriously."},{"time":498250,"text":"When you start to mock them, it hurts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501393,"text":"Now, everybody is talking\nabout His Majesty, the Internet,"},{"time":505043,"text":"and it is also a very useful skill."},{"time":507279,"text":"But don't rush to label things\nlike \"a Facebook Revolution,\""},{"time":511438,"text":"\"Twitter Revolution.\""},{"time":512616,"text":"Don't mix the tools\nwith the substance."},{"time":515999,"text":"It is true that the Internet\nand the new media are very useful"},{"time":519477,"text":"in making things faster and cheaper."},{"time":522034,"text":"They also make it a bit safer\nfor the participants,"},{"time":524881,"text":"because they give partial anonymity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527175,"text":"We're watching the great example\nof something else the Internet can do."},{"time":530825,"text":"It can put the price tag\nof state-sponsored violence"},{"time":534376,"text":"over a nonviolent protester."},{"time":535995,"text":"This is the famous group\n\"We are all Khaled Said,\""},{"time":538495,"text":"made by Wael Ghonim\nin Egypt, and his friend."},{"time":540836,"text":"This is the mutilated face of the guy\nwho was beaten by the police."},{"time":544723,"text":"This is how he became known to the public,"},{"time":546747,"text":"and this is what probably became\nthe straw that broke the camel's back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550882,"text":"But here is also the bad news."},{"time":552597,"text":"The nonviolent struggle is won\nin the real world, in the streets."},{"time":556301,"text":"You will never change\nyour society towards democracy,"},{"time":560492,"text":"or, you know, the economy,\nif you sit down and click."},{"time":563905,"text":"There are risks to be taken,"},{"time":565346,"text":"and there are living people\nwho are winning the struggle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569071,"text":"Well, the million-dollar question."},{"time":570761,"text":"What will happen in the Arab world?"},{"time":572692,"text":"And though young people\nfrom the Arab world"},{"time":574716,"text":"were pretty successful\nin bringing down three dictators,"},{"time":577988,"text":"shaking the region,"},{"time":580408,"text":"kind of persuading the clever kings\nfrom Jordan and Morocco"},{"time":583587,"text":"to do substantial reforms,"},{"time":585406,"text":"it is yet to be seen\nwhat will be the outcome."},{"time":589487,"text":"Whether the Egyptians and Tunisians\nwill make it through the transition,"},{"time":593436,"text":"or this will end in bloody\nethnic and religious conflicts,"},{"time":597071,"text":"whether the Syrians\nwill maintain nonviolent discipline,"},{"time":602317,"text":"faced with a brutal daily violence\nwhich kills thousands already,"},{"time":606141,"text":"or they will slip into violent struggle"},{"time":608276,"text":"and make ugly civil war."},{"time":612689,"text":"Will these revolutions be pushed\nthrough the transitions and democracy"},{"time":616691,"text":"or be overtaken by the military\nor extremists of all kinds?"},{"time":620800,"text":"We cannot tell."},{"time":622894,"text":"The same works for the Western sector,"},{"time":624919,"text":"where you can see\nall these excited young people"},{"time":627209,"text":"protesting around the world,\noccupying this, occupying that."},{"time":631538,"text":"Are they going to become the world wave?"},{"time":634309,"text":"Are they going to find their skills,\ntheir enthusiasm, and their strategy"},{"time":639968,"text":"to find what they really want\nand push for the reform,"},{"time":643262,"text":"or will they just stay complaining\nabout the endless list"},{"time":647515,"text":"of the things they hate?"},{"time":649982,"text":"This is the difference\nbetween the two paths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652774,"text":"Now, what do the statistics have?"},{"time":655597,"text":"My friend Maria Stephan's book"},{"time":658215,"text":"talks a lot about violent\nand nonviolent struggle,"},{"time":660939,"text":"and there are some shocking data."},{"time":663590,"text":"If you look at the last 35 years\nand different social transitions,"},{"time":667876,"text":"from dictatorship to democracy,"},{"time":669742,"text":"you will see that,\nout of 67 different cases,"},{"time":673095,"text":"in 50 of these cases\nit was nonviolent struggle"},{"time":676729,"text":"which was the key power."},{"time":679809,"text":"This is one more reason\nto look at this phenomenon,"},{"time":682452,"text":"this is one more reason\nto look at Generation Y."},{"time":686013,"text":"Enough for me to give them credit,"},{"time":688089,"text":"and hope that they will find their skills\nand their courage"},{"time":692981,"text":"to use nonviolent struggle"},{"time":694668,"text":"and thus fix at least a part of the mess\nour generation is making in this world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699765,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700852,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}